# WatchAgent Classifier Noise Control Rule

When modifying classifier logic:

- Prefer meaningful monitoring signals over small one-reading changes.
- Good event triggers include state changes, compound risk, prolonged conditions, severity increases, and cross-city anomalies.
- Do not assume Open-Meteo updates hourly. Treat the reading timestamp as the source of truth.
- Use time windows instead of fixed reading counts for prolonged or pattern-based events.
- Do not fire context-based events unless enough context exists.
- Avoid repeated alerts for the same city and event type.
- If an event is already active or recently emitted, suppress it unless severity increases.
- Tests must prove both when an event fires and when it does not fire.